The Chicken and Waffles were to die for...

Example of a poorly run business. Came here on Sunday, had to wait for coffee for over 15 min, another 30 min for food. Overall ambience is below average, tasteless, no style, no design, as if they picked all furniture and prints off the curbside trash. No one could take our payment by the register, we could just walk out without paying and no one would notice. On our way out about 20 people were waiting in the hall while there were 7-8 tables available inside, just careless service and a diner food. Do not recommend!

Before going my group called ahead and was told the wait was 30 minutes so we went. We ended up waiting for about an hour to be seated, they had several tables open but said they only seated people they believed they could serve. The line went down the hall and around the corner; none of the staff went to check on the line but kept telling people arriving the wait was 30 minutes. The wait staff tried their best, there was only one person cooking for a busy brunch crowd. The food wasn't terrible but it wasn't as advertised on their social medias, we saw the cook put pancakes in a microwave so there's that too. Proceed with caution, it's a long wait and most people left. Seems the owners don't care enough to manage the place better. We ate and left immediately, I wouldn't say the wait was worth it and will not be returning.

Went for Sunday brunch - the place is OK but not really worth it. Service, atmosphere, and food have a lot of room for improvement.  There was a crowd at the door waiting for tables and no waiter ever came up to say what the wait was or take names. There was plenty of open tables. The couple in front of me got tired of waiting and left. I eventually just sat myself at a table and they served me.  Food was not bad, but not overly tasty. My observation of the kitchen (it’s an open kitchen) seemed to imply that the pancakes and waffles are made from a grocery store box mix (Krusteaz).  Probably wouldn’t go back again.

I would not recommend coming here if you are hungry. They had us wait 30 minutes for a table (they had open tables inside yet we had to wait) and we waited one hour for our food only to realize they forgot about us and kept serving people that got there 20 minutes after us. Very disappointed and hungry. Unfortunately there is only one cook prepping food
Waited for an hour and a half and never got food. Had to just leave to go next door for food. Such a waste of our time.
Such a great little ace. On the 4th floor. Has the best breakfast and lunch. Service is top-notch.

went with my family, sat there for almost 30 minutes and no waitress ever even came to the table. it’s sad because the place seemed like a good spot to grab lunch or breakfast. you can definitely tell they’re more “college kid friendly”  not orientated towards families. wish i could say whether or not the food was good but i never even got to order a drink.
Local, lively and delicious
My roommates and I really enjoyed our brunch here! Even on a busy morning, we only waited 5 minutes for a table, and our food + coffees were yummy.
Cool little spot with tasty eats
Delicious hot chocolate, they make your drink however you want it. The corned beef hash was a great option for breakfast!
The coffee and the cornbeef hash were delicious! Cool atmosphere.

Nice decor and space. I especially liked the outdoor seating. Went on a weekday afternoon not too crowded. Service was veerryyy slow all around. Staff was nice and relatively attentive. We ordered a club sandwich and a chicken quesadilla.  Club was good but severely lacking meat. Really thin and mostly just bread. Quesadilla was really lackluster. For the amount of time it took to prepare I was expecting a whole lot better. Could’ve done way better at home. Don’t get there hungry or you’ll die waiting. Overall food wise it was a disappointing experience.  If they can pick that up they’ll be in really good shape.

WAY over-hyped from tiktok. The outdoor seating is tiny and barely a view, food was mediocre and overpriced, and our waiter told us there was no cold brew when its clearly listed on the coffee menu and online (btw its just buddy brew but charged an extra arm and leg). We waited an hour for our check because our waiter forgot about us. Skip this place for sure!
We came here for a coffee. Sat outside with the beautiful weather. Great view. Drinks were good.

My gf and I were looking for a new coffee place to try! We stopped at The Attic and it was absolutely amazing! We originally stopped for coffee but we ended up having breakfast, no regrets! Absolutely amazing nothing but good things about The Attic. On a side note if you love hash browns you should definitely get some. And café con leche and cinnamon iced it's bomb!
Coolest space in Tampa.

A favorite location for Cafe food. One of the best spots in the area. Looking forward to returning with my coworkers. It has an awesome feel to it. Feeling here is similar to a cafe in San Jose I liked.
Quick service, good food, nice staff. Not expensive.

The atmosphere was super relaxing and just laid back. The outdoor scene was small but cute and private. I loved the attitudes of the staff and how helpful they were. The food was really good, I had the crazy potato which was amazing. And the bottomless mimosas were so worth it! I will definitely be back.

It's not terrible but The Attic definitely misses the mark. First of all, the food just isn't good. We went for brunch and all of our dishes were extremely bland, it should not be hard to make eggs, cheese, and hash browns taste good. Secondly, the decor is really shabby. The instagram photos look great but in person the place looks cheap and dingy. Thirdly, the service was quite poor. Everybody was nice but it seemed like nobody had told the servers anything about the place. There are no cocktail or beer menus at all and when we asked for one we were told that they have "wine and some beers".  Now you might be wondering how in the world a place with this poor of a review got three stars. The saving grace of this place is mostly everything on the menu is under $10 so it's not like you are getting screwed. If you want low priced, low quality food in a low quality setting then you might enjoy the Attic, but I will not be returning.
Good spot
Great little cafe in downtown Tampa with outdoor balcony seating.

1st time I went with my father and a friend; the service was terrible(no napkins, silverware, milk or sugar for coffee was presented had to ask for all of it, both servers were completely forgetful of us), but the food was good.  ---2nd time i went alone to give them another chance it was even worse than the first. Same two lousy servers one had dark complexion and curly hair wearing glasses, other was a fair skinned and blonde kinda athletic looking. Neither of them took my order promply and I was very patient and kind to them. Took 15 minutes for a coffee and water, than 45 minutes for a cuban breakfast sandwich.(which i never received, I just ordered a cuban since it was almost lunch time and probably was faster to get) I wasn't helped by either of the two servers mentioned above. Instead it was another girl who usually works at the register (tattoos and kind of rocker looking) she was super cool and understanding.  I will never give that business another dime of my 💰. If you don't look like a huge meal ticket to either of the two lousy servers mentioned above you will be forgotten about and they will attend everyone else except you.  Cook was nice and register girl was nice. Once again was upset about this service but didn't make a scene. Hope your experience was better than mine.
Great space, great view and better coffee.
I really enjoyed my corned beef hash and my cortado! The service is friendly and the lime trees and outdoor seating are so fun!
Pretty chill spot. It hit the spot for what we needed. Great drinks, decent food, and a great view. Would go back again if it was convenient.
Chicken and waffles were delicious and service was fast and very nice.

I really enjoyed my time at this place. The seating is spaced out so it feels very open and clean. The girl serving us was very nice ! The food was pretty good too. It wasn’t mind blowing. But it was good.

Great location, service, food and ambiance. Went on a Saturday morning and the staff is very friendly and sat us quickly and got our drinks out fast. The veggie omelet was very good and their potion size is good. Prices around $8 as expected for a place like this.

Nice location, pretty views, friendly service, spacing made it seem not-super- crowded. If you like sweet drinks-- delicious & big FROZEN Mimosas (Mango, pineapple, passion fruit-guava, strawberry, etc). Did a paint-sip event, should have waited to order food b/c it got cold--but was piping hot when they brought it out. IMO, Chicken could use more seasoning, & waffles maybe more vanilla extract, or something. Slightly plain, but overall still good. Would go back & maybe try specialty pancakes, & more mimosas. Had food envy from other tables, my friend said her Breakfast Cuban was tasty.  Note: If you aren't super familiar w/downtown (at the time of this post), street parking on Kennedy in front of building is free til 1pm (then $ . 80/hr). Close ~2p on weekends.
Great food. I had the Cuban and flat white. So satisfying.

The cook wasn’t wearing a mask. We waited 40 minutes for our food. People that were sat after us got their food, ate it, and left before we even got our food. Also, the food was mediocre and the coffee was too expensive for the quality/amount. Two stars instead of one because the waitress was really nice and kept apologizing for the food taking so long.
awesome

Cortado Notes  Source: The Attic Cafe in Tampa, Fl  Tactioception: Hot to the touch. The glass enclosure burned my fingers upon first grasp. The burning sensation was oaky, with a bit of first degree burns around the corner. Upon dipping my finger into the actual cortado, the burn was much more mild, complemented by the frothy milk on top, adding a layer of fluffiness to the touch.  Olfacoception : Hints of vanilla at the back end bordering on the sweet to nutty spectrum of flavor with notes of clove, maple syrup, and molasses making up the majority of the body.  Ophthalmoception: A visual spectacle worthy of Martha Stewart, GQ, and Gizmodo front covers. The collection of multicolored frothy swirls is a perfect allegory for the synonymity of man. It's as if the heavens themselves painted this masterpiece to show humanity the pool of Lazarus set in a fantastical utopia.  Audioception: As I bent my humble ear to the source, I heard everything in nothing. Inside was a perfect stillness. The culmination of the efforts and striving and pains of labor that bring about nothing but entropy. The noises I heard were those that people across the world seek their whole life for, captured perfectly in this tiny cup. Absolute perfection.  Gustaoception: Tasted like espresso with warm milk.

My favorite cafe downtown. Rosa the chef is fabulous.  Rich has done a great job building the place into a thriving destination.  Not just for lunch when you are at work; come for brunch on Sunday after church or stop[ up in the evening after a workshop at TampaBay WAvE!
Great place to meet for business and fun

Good location downtown, but hard to find.  Take the elevator to the top floor, and find a quiet open space for lunch or coffee.  The food is not far from what you might find in your own kitchen.  Basic sandwiches and soups, but good and quickly prepared.  Very friendly staff.  Nice alternative to the pricey, crowded, and loud lunchtime eateries.  During nice weather, eat outside on the balconey!
Great place for a cold refreshment!
Great coffee, food, beers, wine and great view

UPDATE:  My only gripe is they now serve burgers for lunch and without the proper ventilation (hood venting system) the place fills with greasy burger smell throughout. Just really destroys the setting when the coffee shop smells like a Five Guys burger joint.  Awesome coffee (Buddy Brew)  Alesi pastries along with simple hot/cold breakfast options.  New 4th floor  space is now open and it is impressive. Great open space and nice views of downtown Tampa with a huge set off east facing window sliders that can be open on those cooler days and nights. Plenty of nature might permeates the space but not in an overwhelming way.  They have draft beers on tap with a small selection of bottled beers and wine to go along with their brew.  Definitely a trendy look and feel but in no way pretentious.
Good coffee, chill atmosphere, serves Alessi Bakery pastries!!
Crazy Hashbrowns are perfect! Get them with jalapeños 👌🏼 Good coffee too
Good coffee and relaxed atmosphere.  My girlfriend enjoyed her taco salad and my cappuccino was perfect.
Great atmosphere, great service, really good food (crazy hash brown) and great coffee!
A well hidden gem.

The atmosphere is great. The food was delicious and they offer the right amount of food on their menu. Plus a special for everyday of the work week. The reason why I am giving it four stars... I left smelling like I have been working there for years. The building needs to provide better ventilation. Very friendly staff. The coffee was excellent. I had a quesadilla and It was great in taste. I am definitely coming back to sit outside because this is a rooftop restaurant and I get nostalgic of my beloved hometown.
Totally cool place, full bar. Very hip, and has an awesome view of downtown. Love coming here to hangout or do homework. Great staff.
Good hot food options.
This was a cute little place in downtown Tampa that I didn't even know existed. Great for after work drinks.
Coffee is good, space has definite potential. Excited to see where they go with it. Definitely need a spot like this downtown.
This place looks and feel pretty cool. The batista is super nice. Awesome place.
Great spot for a beer or coffee. Just getting up and running and has limited food. Decent live music on some nights. Worth a stop.
Amazing list of beers on tap!
